This article is a joint statement from the White House Press Secretary and the 10 Downing Street Spokesperson. It discusses the discussions between President Obama and Prime Minister Brown on various global issues. They agreed on the significance of the steps taken by the G8 and the MEF on climate change, as well as the importance of completing economic and financial reforms agreed upon at the G20 Summit in London. They expressed solidarity on the issue of Iran and condemned the detention of Embassy staff by the Iranian authorities. The Prime Minister also welcomed President Obama's plans for a nuclear security conference in 2010 and both leaders looked forward to staying in close touch in the lead up to the Pittsburgh summit.